description: Global Roads Inventory Project (GRIP 4) Total Roads Density is a raster dataset derived from the Global Roads Inventory Project (GRIP) that represents the density of roads across the globe. This dataset is designed for use in global environmental and biodiversity modeling projects, rather than for navigation purposes. It is based on various sources, including OpenStreetMap, and harmonizes individual source datasets using the UNSDI-Transportation data model. The dataset is provided under an Open Data Commons Open Database License (ODbL) and is free to use.
